         <abstract id="aspace_74214f6cf0ed3f4b6005c5993508539e">Financial records, a diary, and legal documents relating to the Gardner, Pinkham, Swain, and Coffin families of Nantucket. Most prominent in the collection is Silas Gardner, with a diary, bills, and receipts (1776-1822). He was co-owner with his nephew, Paul Pinkham, Jr., of the schooner, <title render="italic">
               <part>Pomona</part>
            </title>, for which there are legal and financial papers. In addition there are papers relating to Grafton Gardner and George Swain, records for the sloop, <title render="italic">
               <part>Caroline</part>
            </title> (1798-1799), and documents concerning the division of the common lands of Nantucket (1663-1806).</abstract>
    
      </did>
